/**
 * Sliding Window Rate Limiting Middleware for Express.js
 *
 * TRUE sliding window: stores the timestamp of every request per client and,
 * on each incoming request, evicts any timestamp older than `windowMs` relative
 * to *now*. The limit is enforced against the count of timestamps remaining in
 * the trailing window. Because the window edge moves continuously with the
 * clock, there is no fixed-interval "reset" boundary a client can burst across
 * (unlike a fixed-window counter).
 *
 * ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
