## Design decisions worth calling out

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **`timestamps[i] < windowStart` (strict `<`)** | Keeps a request made at *exactly* `windowMs` ago; semantically it just entered the window boundary, so excluding it would be surprising. |
| **Linear scan from the front** | Timestamps are always appended in ascending order. The pruned prefix is bounded by `maxRequests` and is usually empty or tiny — O(n) is faster in practice than a binary search with its overhead. |
| **`slice` only when `pruneIdx > 0`** | Avoids a pointless allocation on the hot path when nothing was pruned. |
| **`cleanupTimer.unref()`** | Belt-and-suspenders guard. Without it, a forgotten `close()` call would keep the Node event loop alive indefinitely in tests or after `server.close()`. |
| **`close()` is synchronous** | `clearInterval` is immediate; no async teardown needed. Makes it trivial to use in `afterEach` or `process.on('SIGTERM')` handlers. |
| **`X-RateLimit-Reset` is per-slot, not per-window** | In a sliding window there is no single "reset time" — slots open as individual old requests age out. Reporting when the *oldest* slot opens is the most accurate and most useful signal. |

